source.name: NSF GRFP Awardees And Honorable Mentions (2000-2012)
source.description: The National Science Foundation's (NSF's) Graduate Research Fellowship Program (GRFP) provides three years of support for graduate study leading to research-based masters or doctoral degrees in disciplines relevant to the mission of the Foundation. This dataset includes GRFP Awardees and Honorable Mention recipients for from 2000 to 2012.
